div.p:
Margarite in french signifies a Dazie, which for the allusion to her name, this Queene did giue for her deuise: and this as others more, haue seemed to mee not vnwoorthy the explaning. Now, though no doubt I had need to excuse other things beside, yet these most especially, the rest Iouer-passe to eschue tedious recitall, or to speake as malicious enuie may, for that in truth I ouer-see them. If they bee as harmelesly taken as I meant them, it shall suffise to haue onely tonched the cause of the title, of the dedications, and of the notes, whereby emboldned to publish the residue, (these not beeing accounted in mens opinions 
   〈◊◊〉
) I shall not lastly be afraid to beleeue & acknowledge thee a gentle Reader.
